Preconditions:
The input grid must be a 2-dimensional array.
The grid must contain at least one element.
Each element in the grid must be either 0 or 1, representing connected or disconnected cells respectively.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the minimum number of days required to disconnect the grid.
If the grid is already disconnected, the method should return If it is not possible to disconnect the grid, the method should return -1.